</div>

<div class="content">
  <h2>Understanding Blender Categories</h2>
  <p>Blenders are not one-size-fits-all. Choosing the right one depends on what you plan to make and how much space you have.</p>

  <div class="guide-grid">
    <div class="guide-box">
      <h3>High-Performance</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Examples:</strong> Vitamix, Blendtec</li>
        <li><strong>Best For:</strong> Daily users, large families, making hot soups, nut butters, and the smoothest possible green smoothies. They are expensive but built to last.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="guide-box">
      <h3>Mid-Range</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Examples:</strong> Ninja, KitchenAid</li>
        <li><strong>Best For:</strong> Casual users who want decent power without the premium price tag. Great for basic fruit smoothies, crushing ice, and margaritas.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="guide-box">
      <h3>Personal / Portable</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Examples:</strong> NutriBullet, Magic Bullet</li>
        <li><strong>Best For:</strong> Single servings, quick morning smoothies, and easy cleanup. Ideal for dorms, small apartments, or taking on the go.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="guide-box">
      <h3>Immersion (Hand)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Examples:</strong> Breville, Braun</li>
        <li><strong>Best For:</strong> Pureeing soups directly in the pot, making small batches of mayo or sauces. Easy to store in a drawer.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq-list">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">What is the difference between a high-performance blender and a standard blender?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">High-performance blenders (like Vitamix or Blendtec) typically have motors over 1000 watts and heavy-duty blades, allowing them to pulverize tough ingredients, crush ice instantly, and even heat soups through friction. Standard blenders are less powerful and better suited for basic smoothies and soft ingredients.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">Do I really need a Vitamix or is a Ninja enough?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">It depends on your usage. A Ninja is excellent for most daily tasks like smoothies and frozen drinks at a fraction of the cost. However, a Vitamix offers superior blending smoothness, lasts significantly longer (often decades), and handles difficult tasks like making nut butter more effectively.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">Can personal blenders handle ice and frozen fruit?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Most modern personal blenders, like the higher-end NutriBullets, can handle ice and frozen fruit, but you may need to add more liquid and blend in shorter bursts compared to full-size blenders.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">What is an immersion blender best used for?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">An immersion (or hand) blender is perfect for blending soups directly in the pot, pureeing small batches of sauces or baby food, and making quick emulsions like mayonnaise. It saves you from transferring hot liquids into a countertop blender.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">Are glass blender jars better than plastic?</div>
      <div class="faq-a">Glass jars don't absorb odors or stain and are scratch-resistant, but they are heavy and can break if dropped. Most high-end blenders use BPA-free Tritan plastic because it is incredibly durable, lightweight, and safe for blending hot liquids without shattering.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script is:inline>
  const headers = document.querySelectorAll('th[data-sort]');
  const rows = document.querySelectorAll('.brand-row');
  const tableBody = document.getElementById('tableBody');

  // Sort logic
  headers.forEach(header => {
    header.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const sortType = header.getAttribute('data-sort');
      const isAsc = !header.classList.contains('asc');

      headers.forEach(h => { h.classList.remove('asc', 'desc'); });
      header.classList.add(isAsc ? 'asc' : 'desc');

      const rowsArray = Array.from(rows);

      rowsArray.sort((a, b) => {
        let aVal, bVal;

        if (sortType === 'brand') {
          aVal = a.children[0].innerText.toLowerCase();
          bVal = b.children[0].innerText.toLowerCase();
        } else if (sortType === 'type') {
          aVal = a.children[1].innerText.toLowerCase();
          bVal = b.children[1].innerText.toLowerCase();
        } else if (sortType === 'price') {
          aVal = a.children[2].innerText.length; // Compare number of '$'
          bVal = b.children[2].innerText.length;
        } else if (sortType === 'power') {
          aVal = parseInt(a.children[3].innerText) || 0;
          bVal = parseInt(b.children[3].innerText) || 0;
        } else if (sortType === 'size') {
          aVal = parseInt(a.children[4].innerText) || 0;
          bVal = parseInt(b.children[4].innerText) || 0;
        } else if (sortType === 'speeds') {
          aVal = parseInt(a.children[5].innerText) || 0;
          bVal = parseInt(b.children[5].innerText) || 0;
        } else if (sortType === 'noise') {
          const noiseOrder = { 'quiet': 1, 'moderate': 2, 'loud': 3, 'very loud': 4 };
          aVal = noiseOrder[a.children[6].innerText.toLowerCase()] || 0;
          bVal = noiseOrder[b.children[6].innerText.toLowerCase()] || 0;
        } else if (sortType === 'cleaning') {
          aVal = a.children[7].innerText.toLowerCase();
          bVal = b.children[7].innerText.toLowerCase();
        } else if (sortType === 'warranty') {
          aVal = parseInt(a.children[8].innerText) || 0;
          bVal = parseInt(b.children[8].innerText) || 0;
        }

        if (aVal < bVal) return isAsc ? -1 : 1;
        if (aVal > bVal) return isAsc ? 1 : -1;
        return 0;
      });

      rowsArray.forEach(row => tableBody.appendChild(row));
    });
  });
</script>

</SiteLayout>
